thread.title: Car rental shop to open in former restaurant space near Dayton Mall
thread.title_full: Car rental shop to open in former restaurant space near Dayton Mall

author: Tristan Navera
title: Car rental shop to open in former restaurant space near Dayton Mall
text:
Tristan Navera Staff Reporter Dayton Business Journal Tristan Navera Staff Reporter Dayton Business Journal A car rental company is planning to move its offices near the Dayton Mall. A car rental company is planning to move its offices near the Dayton Mall . Enterprise Rent-A-Car is moving its offices near the Dayton Mall from 123 North Springboro Pike down the road into the former Friendly's restaurant at 8270 N. Springboro Pike, employees confirmed. That location is one of about a dozen in the Miami Valley for the large car-rental chain. All local Friendly's restaurants closed late last year suddenly, with most of the five locations remaining empty buildings. It would be a re-use of a larger and more prominent commercial space for the rental car company, which is currently housed in a strip mall. Company officials could not provide more details on the move.
